\f0\b\fs36 \cf0 What is Scrivener?\
\pard\tx560\tx1120\tx1680\tx2240\tx2800\tx3360\tx3920\tx4480\tx5040\tx5600\tx6160\tx6720\pardeftab720\sl336\slmult1\sb260\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf0 Scrivener is aimed at writers of all stripes\'97novelists, journalists, academics, screenwriters, playwrights\'97who need to structure a long piece of text. Scrivener is a ring-binder, a scrapbook, a corkboard, an outliner and a text editor all rolled into one. It is primarily intended as a first draft tool, a kind of writer\'92s shed for those of us who don\'92t have a spare shed.\
Below you\'92ll find a brief survey of the key concepts behind Scrivener\'97the ideas that led me to drop my pen, learn programming, and create Scrivener in the first place. If you\'92re a user of the desktop version, you\'92re no doubt familiar with much of this already, in which case you can happily skip this section (or you can skip it grumpily\'97in Scrivener, how you work is entirely up to you).\
