\f1\b0\fs26 \cf0 Conventional word processors are wonderful for all kinds of things, but I\'92ve always struggled with them when it comes to writing long texts, because I like to jump around, writing different sections as they come to me. Scrivener makes it easy to compose in any order you want, whether that\'92s from start to finish or completely at random.\
Word processors only ever know about the document you\'92re working on at any one time\'97if you have lots of different documents pertaining to a single project, it\'92s up to you to keep track of them. By contrast, Scrivener is a project-based app, and each project you create in Scrivener can contain as many documents as you desire. This means that you can write in chunks as large or small as you wish. If you\'92re writing a novel, for instance, you could write each chapter in a separate document, or you could break it down further and write each 
\f2\i scene
\f1\i0  in a different document\'97it\'92s up to you. When you come to export or print your work, all of those myriad sections can be compiled into a single document.\
